 moderate (T < 1300 K) heating and energetic ion sputtering due to a stellar\nsuperflare from the F4V primary are consistent with the observations. The space\nweathered patina should be reddened, contain copious amounts of nanophase Fe,\nand should be transient on timescales of decades unless replenished.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 15 Mar 2020 17:09:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
